Description: TOFA's - Token of Appreciation vision is to transform the World, one connection at a time.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Jo Englesson, heir to Swedish furniture manufacturer, Englesson.com, announced the launch of TOFA, a Token of Appreciation, on Thursday, June 26, 2008. Dedication of the first "Giving Year" began at noon, exactly one year from the idea's inception. TOFA was inspired on June 26, 2007 when Jo Englesson, not paying attention, plowed into Don Warms while traveling through an airport, nearly knocking them both to the ground. After assuring Jo he was not angry or hurt, the octogenarian joked with Englesson that she probably did it all the time. Relieved, Englesson said goodbye and watched Mr. Warms walking away, all the while searching her pockets for something she could give the gentleman as a token of her appreciation for his kindness. Realizing she had nothing to give him, she began to form an idea to create something that would encapsulate gratitude. "What if I had a token that had the power to thank someone for what they did or said to make a difference? A token that said it all," says Englesson, a soft-spoken, Swedish blonde who received her education as an economist from Loyola Marymount University in Los Angeles. "What if I could change the world one connection at a time? That day, TOFA was born. TOFA's strength lies in the Token Tracking System. Once given, the coins can be passed along to individuals as appreciation and may be tracked online via their unique serial numbers at TOFA's website, www.tofa.us. At the dedication on June 26th, Don Warms received the Number 1 TOFA coin cast in silver and became the first Honorary VIP Member for Life. This also initiated the first "Giving Year," where Englesson has documented her experience of giving one token a day for 365 days — inspiring others to see the value of gratitude and begin their own "Giving Year." TOFA's goal is to generate a social awareness conversation in the world through daily connections via the tokens and the website. TOFA aims to have 1,000,000 tokens in circulation by December 2012.

Description: StatBroadcast’s statmonitr media stats platform.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: StatBroadcast® Systems is a sports statistics technology and media relations partner for athletic programs and events.They  help deliver and distribute real-time statistics information from sports events to a variety of different platforms and audiences. StatBroadcast® Systems has been providing technology and media relations support for athletic events and programs for the past 13 academic years. It began in its current form in 2004 under the name StatDisplay, with its first two clients, the Fiesta Bowl and Arizona State University, as a media relations partner that assisted with the setup and administration of information technology at athletic events, including specifically live stat monitors for the media and staff. In preparation to host the 2007 BCS National Title Game, StatDisplay became BCS Stats Systems in 2006 and developed the first version of the product known today as StatMonitr. StatBroadcast®'s launch of its newly designed graphical interface for its stats feeds in 2016 is the fourth generation of its platform, with each generation building and expanding upon the previous while incorporating new technological innovations in web design. The latest platform includes fully responsive ad pages that adapt and resize themselves to fit your screen and even your browser window when you resize it. Since that time, StatBroadcast® has grown into the leading provider of statistics technologies for collegiate athletics nationwide, and expanded its product lines to include StatMonitr wireless screens, StatMonitr web stats and StatBroadcast® Live for the web, mobile phones and multimedia. StatBroadcast® now provides support for more than 35 college football bowl games, over 250 NCAA athletic programs, has expanded into the NAIA and NJCAA junior college markets and the high school markets at both the regular season and state championship levels, 30 conferences, the College Football Playoffand NCAA championship events, spanning all three Divisions.
